---
import Layout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageTitle = "The Adaptive Voice Framework (AVF) | Ted's Voice Academy";
const pageDescription = "AVF: The owner's manual your voice never came with. A comprehensive framework bridging science, somatics, and soul for singers, speakers, and voice teachers.";
const amazonLink = "https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GD2SH8J5";
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription}>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="avf-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-content">
          <h1 class="hero-title">AVF: The Adaptive Voice Framework</h1>
          <p class="hero-subtitle">The owner's manual your voice never came with</p>
          <p class="hero-body">The voice is a fluid, balanced system driven by expressive intent. When you understand how it works, everything else falls into place — technique, style, expression, health.</p>
          <p class="hero-body">I developed the Adaptive Voice Framework over four decades of teaching, performing, and studying with master teachers across every vocal tradition. AVF brings together voice science, physical awareness, and artistic expression into one clear picture — a framework that makes sense of every methodology and every genre.</p>
          <p class="hero-body">This isn't another method competing for your loyalty. It's the owner's manual that helps you understand what you already have.</p>
          <div class="hero-ctas">
            <a href={amazonLink} class="cta-button primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Get Your Copy on Amazon</a>
            <a href="#what-is-avf" class="cta-button secondary">Learn More ↓</a>
          </div>
          <p class="book-specs">Nearly 700 pages · Paperback $42.95 · Kindle $9.99</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-image">
          <img src="/images/avf-book-cover.png" alt="The Adaptive Voice Framework book cover" class="book-cover" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Is AVF Section -->
  <section id="what-is-avf" class="avf-section what-is-avf">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>A framework that makes sense of them all</h2>
      <p>Over the years, I studied with dozens of teachers across every major vocal tradition — Bel canto, Estill, Speech Level Singing, Alexander Technique, and more. Each approach offered real insight. Each had something valuable to teach.</p>
      <p>But I kept noticing something: the best ideas connected. What seemed like contradictions were often the same principle seen from different angles. The more I learned, the more I saw a coherent picture emerging underneath.</p>
      <p>AVF is that picture. It explains the universal principles that make voices function well — across every style, genre, and context. Classical, contemporary, musical theater, speech, podcast. The foundations are the same.</p>
      <p>When you understand these foundations, techniques that seemed contradictory start to connect. You see why certain approaches work for certain goals. You gain the clarity to make good choices for your voice — or to help your students make good choices for theirs.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Five Pillars Section -->
  <section class="avf-section pillars-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>The Five Pillars — foundations every healthy voice shares</h2>
      <div class="pillars-grid">
        <div class="pillars-content">
          <p class="intro">Regardless of style, every sustainable voice rests on these same foundations:</p>
          <div class="pillar-list">
            <div class="pillar-item">
              <h3>Body Organization</h3>
              <p>The way your body is organized shapes everything that follows.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-item">
              <h3>Breath Mechanics</h3>
              <p>The engine that powers your voice.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-item">
              <h3>Phonation</h3>
              <p>How your vocal folds create tone.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-item">
              <h3>Resonance</h3>
              <p>How that tone is shaped and amplified.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar-item">
              <h3>Expression</h3>
              <p>The artistic and emotional intent that brings it all to life.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="outro">These pillars work together as a balanced system. When one is out of alignment, the others compensate. Understanding this relationship gives you a clear starting point for growth — and helps you identify what's actually happening when something feels off.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillars-image">
          <img src="/images/avf-pillars.png" alt="The Five Pillars of the Adaptive Voice Framework" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Eight Dials Section -->
  <section class="avf-section dials-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>The Eight Dials — settings that create stylistic variety</h2>
      <div class="dials-grid">
        <div class="dials-image">
          <img src="/images/avf-dials.png" alt="The Eight Dials of the Adaptive Voice Framework" />
        </div>
        <div class="dials-content">
          <p class="intro">While the pillars provide stability, the dials provide fluidity. These are the variables that let you shift your voice to fit different styles, contexts, and artistic choices:</p>
          <div class="dials-list">
            <div class="dial-item"><strong>Intensity</strong> — dynamic range and power</div>
            <div class="dial-item"><strong>Adduction</strong> — vocal fold closure patterns</div>
            <div class="dial-item"><strong>Onset/Release</strong> — how tones begin and end</div>
            <div class="dial-item"><strong>Laryngeal Height</strong> — vertical positioning of the larynx</div>
            <div class="dial-item"><strong>Resonance Shape</strong> — vowel tuning and tonal color</div>
            <div class="dial-item"><strong>Twang</strong> — brightness and presence</div>
            <div class="dial-item"><strong>Diction</strong> — articulatory clarity</div>
            <div class="dial-item"><strong>Vibrato</strong> — oscillation characteristics</div>
          </div>
          <p class="master-dial">Above them all sits the <strong>Master Dial: Emotional Intent</strong> — the primary driver that coordinates everything else. The voice organizes itself around what you're trying to express. When intention leads, technique follows.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who It's For Section -->
  <section class="avf-section who-section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>Who this framework is for</h2>
      <div class="audience-grid">
        <div class="audience-card">
          <h3>Singers</h3>
          <p>of any genre who want to understand their instrument — with the freedom to cross styles safely and the knowledge to keep growing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <h3>Voice teachers</h3>
          <p>looking for a framework that explains why different approaches work, and how to apply them with clarity across every student you encounter.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <h3>Speakers and professionals</h3>
          <p>who rely on their voice daily and want it to function reliably, clearly, and authentically — without strain.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="audience-card">
          <h3>Anyone</h3>
          <p>ready to understand their voice as a fluid, balanced system — and develop a relationship with it that lasts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Book Section -->
  <section class="avf-section book-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>The Book</h2>
      <div class="book-grid">
        <div class="book-image">
          <img src="/images/avf-book-photo.png" alt="The Adaptive Voice Framework book" />
        </div>
        <div class="book-content">
          <p class="book-title-display">AVF: The Adaptive Voice Framework</p>
          <p class="book-subtitle-display">Bridging Science, Somatics, and Soul</p>
          <p>This is the complete framework — nearly 700 pages covering everything from the science of vocal function to practical application across every genre and context. Written at a collegiate level but designed to be accessible, it's the canonical reference for anyone serious about understanding the voice.</p>
          <div class="whats-inside">
            <h3>What's inside:</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>The Five Pillars and Eight Dials explained in depth</li>
              <li>Cross-genre applications from classical to contemporary</li>
              <li>Gender-affirming voice protocols and aging voice strategies</li>
              <li>Seven practical appendices with diagnostic tools and lesson templates</li>
              <li>100+ sources grounded in voice science and pedagogy</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="formats">
            <p><strong>Formats:</strong></p>
            <p>Paperback — $42.95<br />Kindle — $9.99</p>
            <p class="published">Published December 2025</p>
          </div>
          <a href={amazonLink} class="cta-button primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Order on Amazon</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Learn With Ted Section -->
  <section class="avf-section learn-section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>Learn the framework directly</h2>
      <p>The book gives you the complete picture. Working with me brings it to life.</p>
      <p>I offer private coaching for singers and speakers, ensemble workshops, and group training — all grounded in AVF principles. Whether you're developing your own voice or learning to teach others, I can help you put this framework into practice.</p>
      <div class="learn-ctas">
        <a href="/pricing" class="cta-button primary">Explore Coaching Options</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="cta-button secondary">Contact me about workshops</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA Section -->
  <section class="avf-section final-cta">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2>Your voice didn't come with an owner's manual. Until now.</h2>
      <p>AVF gives you a way to understand what's happening when you sing or speak — and the tools to keep growing. Whether you're a beginner finding your voice or a professional refining your craft, this framework meets you where you are.</p>
      <a href={amazonLink} class="cta-button primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Get Your Copy on Amazon</a>
      <p class="contact-line">Questions about the framework? Email <a href="mailto:AVF@tedsvoiceacademy.com">AVF@tedsvoiceacademy.com</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

